  "text": "Recently, [CITATION_1] presented an unsupervised, HMM-based model for Hebrew morphological disambiguation, using a morphological analyzer as the only resource. A morpheme-based model learns both segmentation and tagging in parallel from a large (6M words) un-annotated corpus. Reported results are 92.32% for POS tagging and 88.5% for full morphological disambiguation. We refer to this result as the state of the art and use the same data for evaluation.",
